##Wuhan anti-epidemic Nurses: Today the most happy is finally happy to wash a face

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Han Yuting, correspondent, Li Junping, _ thepaper.cn _

On February 15th, Peng Jing, a nurse at the 120 first aid station of Hankou Hospital in Wuhan, was on the front line of the epidemic for 30 days. One of the things that pleased her most today was that she felt like "I finally washed my face happily. "

As an emergency room nurse, for 30 days, she has been on the front lines of the fight against the epidemic, every day in the face of the struggle between life and death of the new pneumonia patients, check equipment, infusion, dispensing, injection, bed, dressing... . Rise early, rise late, don't dare to relax.

"All I did was what I was supposed to do, just do my job, " Peng Jing, 35, told thepaper.cn.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For 30 days, Peng Jing, a nurse at the first aid station of Hankou Hospital in Wuhan, has been on the frontline of fighting the epidemic.

First Line of defense after surgery

At the end of 2019, Peng Jing felt that her vision in her left eye had decreased and her vision range was limited. After examination, she suffered from Iris Synechia and needed surgery urgently. Recommended by a local ophthalmologist, she found a leading specialist in Uveitis.

On Jan. 13 and 15, she underwent two separate operations at Chongqing First Affiliated Hospital, where doctors advised her to take some time off before going to work.

At that time, when the epidemic spread in Wuhan, Wuhan Hankou Hospital influx of many patients to consult, see colleagues busy, Peng Jing decided to rush back to Wuhan and colleagues together.

On the afternoon of January 16, when the review was over, she immediately decided to rush back to Wuhan. During the Spring Festival travel rush, the bullet train from Chongqing to Wuhan was sold out, and she managed to board a train ticket from Chongqing to Fengdu in the last five minutes.

Peng Jing recalled that after getting on the bus, she cried for joy and returned to Wuhan the next day, she went to the hospital to work.

As a nurse in the 120th aid station, she usually works for 24 hours before leaving work. She can not eat on time and can not sleep well.

When the head of the hospital heard that she had just had surgery, advised her to rest, she said it was a minor operation, do not rest.

Wuhan Hankou Hospital, as a designated hospital for the treatment of new coronary pneumonia, undertakes a large number of admission and treatment tasks, protective materials are extremely scarce. In order to save goggles, Peng Jing can only use 84 disinfection solution sterilization, so it can be used repeatedly, but the chlorine produced by 84 disinfection solution will irritate the eyes, it is extremely uncomfortable, whenever she finished saving patients, can only use hormone eye drops to reduce discomfort.

What made her sick was that every time she got back from the car, she couldn't wash her face with water, so she had to take a washcloth and wipe her face. Every time she got off work, she felt sticky and burnt on her face.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Peng Jing and her colleagues at Hankou Hospital in Wuhan.

Maximum 96 hours of continuous work

January 19, this day was originally a rest day for Peng Jing. On the same day, a young nurse had an emergency. At this time, the hospital was at a critical moment in the fight against the epidemic. It was the time when the staff was employed. Peng Jing saw that she was very worried and offered to cover the shift, since then, she has volunteered to cover for her colleagues many times.

When asked why she volunteered to cover for her colleagues when her eyes desperately needed a break, she replied: "I'm their oldest sister and a party member. I should set an example. "

The longest shift Peng earned during the epidemic was from Jan. 23 to Jan. 26, when she nearly always drove from the hospital, working 96 hours before and after returning home to rest.

Once, because she had not washed her hair for a long time, she could not help but wash it once with a swimming-glass. She did not think that because she had not taken a rest for a long time, her resistance had dropped. After washing her hair that time, she developed symptoms of a cold and cough. She was worried about catching a new coronary pneumonia, i went to the hospital for a CT scan, but luckily the results were normal.

Peng Jing lived far away from the hospital, Wuhan "closed city" , the city traffic control, let her work extremely inconvenient.

Although the hospital provided temporary accommodation for the staff, she did not apply and felt that it should be reserved for more staff who lived far away.

"I can make do in the on-call room, " Peng said.

In order to catch the hospital bus, every morning, she has to get up at 5:30, off-duty bus, even if the normal work, she usually came home at 8 o'clock at night.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"I am especially moved to see my colleagues all working together and actively in the front line. If others can insist, I will certainly insist. My requirements are not much. As long as I can wash my face and hair normally, I will be satisfied, " Peng said.

This issue is edited by Xing Tan
